24:01.106 --> 24:04.508
- Oh, what's up, Benny?
- Hey, Ty. You okay?

24:04.542 --> 24:06.777
I mean with what happened today,
missing practice and everything.

24:06.811 --> 24:08.545
Oh, you wouldn't
believe me if I told you.

24:08.580 --> 24:11.148
Try me. We're on the same team, right?

24:11.182 --> 24:14.184
Yeah.

24:14.219 --> 24:16.387
Yeah, man. I suppose we are.

24:16.443 --> 24:18.074
I mean, one of us messes up,

24:18.098 --> 24:19.629
we all pay.

24:19.860 --> 24:21.795
That's what went down
today anyway, right?

24:21.893 --> 24:24.728
All right, listen, guys. I'm sorry
you had to run suicides, okay?

24:24.763 --> 24:27.331
- I didn't mean to...
- You didn't mean to what?

24:27.365 --> 24:29.600
Miss practice? Hit that kid?

24:29.634 --> 24:32.002
Miss those two easy boards
against Waverly?

24:32.037 --> 24:33.671
Look, what the hell are you guys doing?

24:33.705 --> 24:35.572
We're going to state finals
next week, and we're concerned

24:35.607 --> 24:37.007
that you're gonna be
screwing it up for us.

24:37.042 --> 24:38.776
No, listen, I promise I won't...

25:29.876 --> 25:32.144
I chatted up the wedding planner,
but she doesn't have the cash.

25:33.146 --> 25:34.980
- Okay, so who does?
- The maid of honor.

25:35.014 --> 25:36.948
Apparently, she insisted.

25:36.983 --> 25:39.418
Linda did not appreciate her bossiness.

25:39.452 --> 25:41.520
Okay. Linda's the wedding planner?

25:41.554 --> 25:43.855
Uh-huh. And Delia...
that's the maid of honor...

25:43.890 --> 25:46.858
is the thorn in Linda's side,
treats her like the help,

25:46.893 --> 25:49.528
is always putting her nose
in other people's business,

25:49.562 --> 25:52.230
and has resting basic face.

25:52.265 --> 25:54.199
Is that a thing?

25:56.402 --> 25:58.470
No, but it should be.

26:02.108 --> 26:03.208
Liam, thank you.

26:04.210 --> 26:05.210
For what?

26:08.614 --> 26:10.115
For helping me with all of this.

26:11.651 --> 26:13.919
For never asking any questions

26:13.953 --> 26:15.454
or second-guessing me.

26:17.990 --> 26:19.858
Not ever, really.

26:22.195 --> 26:23.695
Thank you for just being you.

26:26.933 --> 26:28.099
You make it easy.

26:47.520 --> 26:49.321
You remember the first time we met?

26:49.355 --> 26:52.390
Of course. I was
trying to get into Aperture.

26:52.425 --> 26:55.026
With that horrible Utah ID.

26:55.061 --> 26:58.063
Well, someone was busting my
chops, asking for my zodiac sign.

26:58.097 --> 26:59.965
Vertigo. You said vertigo.

27:02.001 --> 27:03.001
It made you smile.

27:04.136 --> 27:05.270
Yeah, it very much did.

27:07.106 --> 27:08.740
Hey, but you didn't let me in.

27:08.774 --> 27:10.442
Well, that would've been malpractice.

27:11.444 --> 27:13.578
- But you came back.
- With a better ID.

27:13.613 --> 27:15.647
Massachusetts. Land of Lincoln.

27:19.085 --> 27:20.752
Listen.

27:20.786 --> 27:24.389
I know I don't come from money
or class like you do...

27:24.423 --> 27:26.391
but if you give me a chance,

27:26.425 --> 27:27.759
I'll keep you safe.

27:28.995 --> 27:30.595
I'll do what I can to make you happy.

27:33.132 --> 27:34.332
I'll love you.

27:36.035 --> 27:37.035
Always.

27:54.420 --> 27:55.720
Tandy?

27:55.755 --> 27:57.389
Are... are you okay?

27:58.991 --> 28:00.492
Tandy, what?

28:00.526 --> 28:01.526
Umm...

28:02.562 --> 28:04.329
I have to... I have to go.

28:12.405 --> 28:14.806
Ah.

28:39.398 --> 28:41.066
Hey, Ma.

28:41.100 --> 28:44.102
No, no, Coach kept us late running.
He was in a mood.

28:45.905 --> 28:47.372
Yeah, it still kinda is,

28:47.406 --> 28:49.908
so, uh, might not be back for a bit.

28:52.545 --> 28:54.012
Yeah, of course I'll stay safe.

29:09.595 --> 29:12.297
Excuse me. Are you okay?

29:12.331 --> 29:14.966
Yeah. I'm fine.

29:16.736 --> 29:18.303
Sorry, was I making a scene?

29:18.337 --> 29:21.106
No, not at all. You look sad.

29:21.140 --> 29:23.208
God! I'm such a...

29:23.242 --> 29:25.276
No, you're not. What's wrong?

29:31.283 --> 29:32.817
I run away from everything.

29:34.286 --> 29:36.087
I mean, whenever anything
goes wrong or...

29:37.490 --> 29:40.925
hell, goes right,
I... I hightail it outta town.

29:42.228 --> 29:45.130
- Sometimes literally.
- I get it. I do it too.

29:46.365 --> 29:49.401
- It's kind of you to say, but...
- No, I swear to God.

29:49.435 --> 29:51.970
You know I switched my major four times?

29:52.004 --> 29:54.239
- Where'd you go to school?
- Tulane.

29:54.273 --> 29:56.107
- Is that how you met Lynn?
- Yeah.

29:56.142 --> 29:59.077
- How about you?
- Obligatory distant cousin.

29:59.111 --> 30:01.079
- Ah.
- So, what'd you land on?

30:01.113 --> 30:02.580
For a major?

30:02.615 --> 30:04.115
Clinical psychology.

30:04.150 --> 30:07.152
Oh. Well, definitely broke
down in the right place.

30:07.186 --> 30:08.987
Huh! I don't know about all that.

30:09.021 --> 30:11.122
I'm still limited
to the basic questions.

30:11.148 --> 30:12.701
- Like what?
- Like...

30:12.779 --> 30:14.912
"Tell me about your father and mother."

30:17.263 --> 30:20.865
The first one's dead, and the
second one is killing me.

30:20.900 --> 30:22.367
Is that what's upsetting you right now?

30:23.602 --> 30:25.070
No.

30:25.104 --> 30:27.439
No, there's this boy out there
who wants nothing more

30:27.473 --> 30:29.207
than to spend his whole life with me.

30:29.241 --> 30:31.543
- Sounds horrible.
- Right?

30:31.577 --> 30:33.511
Me? All I could do is run away.

30:37.616 --> 30:39.350
Maybe my Mom was right about me.

30:40.352 --> 30:42.721
Okay, I need you to do me a favor.

30:42.755 --> 30:45.890
Get it together, fix your mascara,

30:45.925 --> 30:47.792
and do something
that'll make you happy...

30:47.827 --> 30:51.196
tonight. Drink, dance...

30:51.230 --> 30:53.498
and worry about the rest
of your life tomorrow.

30:53.532 --> 30:55.200
Can you do that for me?

30:56.902 --> 30:58.002
Yeah.

30:59.038 --> 31:00.405
Yeah, I can do that.

31:03.142 --> 31:04.342
You feel better now?

31:08.114 --> 31:10.181
I really, really do.

32:10.643 --> 32:12.911
Thank you for everything.

32:12.945 --> 32:15.547
People went crazy over
those figs in a blanket.

32:15.581 --> 32:16.581
Here.

32:27.459 --> 32:28.459
We gotta go.

32:35.234 --> 32:37.468
- Come on.
- What's up?

32:37.503 --> 32:38.970
Resting basic face is onto us.

32:40.206 --> 32:41.439
We gotta bounce.

32:51.313 --> 32:54.453
No way. No way!

32:54.523 --> 32:56.591
I told you he was trouble.

32:56.626 --> 32:58.994
From day one, girl.

32:59.028 --> 33:01.730
Yeah, I didn't. Hold on.

33:03.799 --> 33:05.400
Sorry, I'll just be...

33:06.502 --> 33:10.572
I swear to Saint Francis
I just had a $20 bill.

33:24.387 --> 33:26.187
Can I get a fifth
of the O'Harrens, please?

33:33.095 --> 33:34.996
- Hey.
- Hey, Mom.

33:35.031 --> 33:37.032
- Sorry I missed dinner.
- Don't sweat it.

33:37.066 --> 33:38.867
Thanks for calling to check in.

33:38.901 --> 33:39.901
Yeah.

33:47.476 --> 33:49.210
- Hey, Ma?
- Yes, sweetheart?

33:51.814 --> 33:52.814
How do you do it?

33:54.450 --> 33:57.185
How do you keep it all together?

33:57.219 --> 34:00.455
Keep everything running like clockwork
after all we've been through?

34:02.325 --> 34:04.559
We're not the first to suffer.
We won't be the last.

34:06.963 --> 34:08.663
You're probably too young
to remember this,

34:08.697 --> 34:10.431
but a while back I wasn't together

34:10.466 --> 34:12.600
by any definition.

34:13.902 --> 34:16.871
But after some time,
I came to a conclusion.

34:18.007 --> 34:20.574
- What was that?
- I had to put it away.

34:22.411 --> 34:24.411
All the anxiety, all of the guilt.

34:25.915 --> 34:28.016
If I couldn't...

34:28.050 --> 34:30.185
